{"id":24306,"date":"2017-01-27T14:57:14","date_gmt":"2017-01-27T10:57:14","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/?p=24306"},"modified":"2024-08-18T14:46:16","modified_gmt":"2024-08-18T10:46:16","slug":"sincerity-muslims-hellfire-forever","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/01\/27\/sincerity-muslims-hellfire-forever\/","title":{"rendered":"Hadith on Ikhlaas: Sincere Muslims do not stay in Hellfire forever"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>&#8216;Itban ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, came to me one morning and a man said, \u201cWhere is Malik ibn al-Dukhshun?\u201d Another man among us said, \u201cThat one is a hypocrite! He does not love Allah and His Messenger!\u201d The Prophet said to him, \u201c<strong>Do you not agree that he says there is no God but Allah, seeking thereby of the countenance of Allah<\/strong>?\u201d The man said, \u201cOf course.\u201d The Prophet said, \u201c<strong>Verily, a servant is not brought on the Day of Resurrection saying so but that Allah will forbid him from entering the Hellfire<\/strong>.\u201d<\/p>\n<p>Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 6938, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 33<\/p>\n<p>Grade: <strong><em>Muttafaqun Alayhi<\/em><\/strong> (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim<\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: right;\">\u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u0650\u062a\u0652\u0628\u064e\u0627\u0646\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u063a\u064e\u062f\u064e\u0627 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064e \u0631\u064e\u0633\u064f\u0648\u0644\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650 \u0648\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0641\u064e\u0642\u0